FBIS4-19844 "drweu079_h_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-079 Daily Report 24 Apr 1994 GERMANY Kinkel Invites Freed PRC Dissident to Bonn Kinkel Invites Freed PRC Dissident to Bonn AU2404130694 Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network in German 1100 GMT 24 Apr 94 AU2404130694 Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network German BFN [Text] FRG Foreign Minister Kinkel has invited released Chinese dissident Wang and his wife to visit Bonn. As the Foreign Ministry reported this morning, the wife of the regime critic confirmed that her husband had been released from prison on bail to receive medical treatment in the United States. Wang, one of the leaders of the 1989 democracy movement, which was bloodily crushed, had been sentenced to 13 years' imprisonment. Kinkel had repeatedly advocated Wang's release.
